Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=12}===============================DIALOGUE============================
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.06,0:02:00.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Robin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.98,0:02:04.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Was my mother here? - OG}Was my mom here?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.48,0:02:10.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What are you saying? There's no way\Nthat your mother is on Ohara, right? - OG}What are you saying?\NWhy would your mother be on Ohara?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.57,0:02:12.95,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,...I must sever ties.{Enies 08 - 29:25}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.95,0:02:16.45,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't make her the daughter of a criminal. - OG}I can't let her become known\Nas a criminal's daughter.{Evo: edited it to match my edit in EL8}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.53,0:02:19.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's this about all of a sudden?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.41,0:02:21.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Y-Yeah... - OG}W-Well...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.25,0:02:22.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right! There's trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:28.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I heard that Marine battleships are coming.\NThey’re gonna arrest all the scholars on the island! - OG}I heard that Marine battleships are coming\Nto arrest all the scholars here!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.71,0:02:31.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is there a disturbance or\Nsomething happening in town? - OG}Is the town blowing things out of proportion?{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.05,0:02:33.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:35.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That isn't a battleship. -OG}There are no battleships.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.76,0:02:39.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We heard that a government\Nship just arrived on this island. -OG}We did hear about\Na government ship making landfall,{Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:43.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll probably be a more rigorous\Ninvestigation than ever. -OG}but it's for an investigation,\Nlikely more rigorous than ever.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.89,0:02:47.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Listen, Robin,\Neven if the government comes here, - OG}Listen, Robin, although\Nthe government representatives are here,{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:51.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{you absolutely cannot tell them\Nyou're an archaeologist. - OG}you absolutely cannot tell them\Nthat you're an archaeologist.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.40,0:02:56.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since you're small, no one will think\Nthat you're a scholar. Got that? - OG}Since you're such a small child, no one will\Nthink that you're a scholar. Understood?{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:02:59.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:04.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Stop what you're doing!\NGet outside with your hands in the air! - OG}Stop what you're doing!\NHands in the air, and step outside!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.96,0:03:07.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Now, that's going too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:12.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This Ohara lab is suspected of a serious crime – deciphering poneglyphs! - OG}{\q2}The Ohara Research Center is suspected\Nof a criminal offense: deciphering poneglyphs!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:16.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We must conduct a thorough search,\Nso everyone outside. Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.01,0:03:19.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Treat this place with care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:23.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The treasures kept here are\Nmore valuable than you can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.35,0:03:25.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We have no obligation to listen to you! - OG}You're wasting your breath!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.39,0:03:26.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Take them outside! - OG}Get him out!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.39,0:03:27.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Yes, sir!\N– Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:29.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To all the townspeople! - OG}Listen up, townspeople!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.61,0:03:35.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We now suspect that this island's scholars\Nare devils who wish to destroy the world! - OG}{\q2}It is our suspicion that the scholars of this island\Nare devils plotting to destroy the world!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.45,0:03:36.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.82,0:03:41.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're world-class scholars and the pride of this island! - OG}They're world-renowned scholars\Nand the pride of this island!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:45.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Consequently, we'll conduct\Na large-scale search of the entire island! - OG}{We will be conducting a large-scale\Nsearch throughout the whole island! - Evo}And so, we will conduct an extensive\Nsearch of the entire island!{Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.66,0:03:49.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{During that time, those who have\Nnothing to do with archaeology - OG}In the meantime, those\Nuninvolved in archaeology{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.04,0:03:53.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{are expected to be carrying an ID and temporarily take refuge on the evacuation ship on the western shore. - OG}will prove it with identification and board\Nthe evacuation ship at the western shore!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.63,0:03:56.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{An evacuation ship?! Is that really necessary?! - OG}{Why would we need an evacuation ship? - Z}An evacuation ship?\NIs that really necessary?{Evo: I prefer the construction with two separate phrases to really hammer home the surprise at hearing the words "evacuation ship". I'll replace the interrobangs though.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:59.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,If it's the scholars' problem,\Nwe have nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:02.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So there should be no need\Nfor us to leave the island. - OG}{We shouldn't need to leave the island. - Z}We shouldn't be required to leave the island.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:04.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's our duty to pass that message to you. - OG}It's merely our duty\Nto pass that message to you.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.18,0:04:09.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What happens to those\Nwho ignore our warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.02,0:04:12.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,is none of our concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.15,0:04:19.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Leave town!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.11,0:04:20.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Evacuate to the western shore!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.78,0:04:23.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The World Government is up to something!
Comment: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:27.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ahhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:31.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm shot! Th-This is the end!\NI'm a goner, dammit! - OG}I've been shot! Th-This is the end!\NI'm a goner, dammit!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.79,0:04:33.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Tell the bosses… - OG}Tell the higher-ups...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.71,0:04:36.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{my position as chief… \Ngive it to my boy! - OG}to give my position as chief to my boy!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:38.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chief, please take a close look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.59,0:04:41.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The bullet barely grazed your jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:42.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.47,0:04:47.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I won't miss next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:52.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, well… What a coincidence to encounter\Nhere the skillful fugitive who escaped... - OG}Well, if it isn't the fugitive\Nwho craftily escaped the Marines' prison!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.56,0:04:56.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the Marines' prison, don’t you think… Nico Olvia? - OG}Fancy seeing {\i1}you{\i0} on this island, Nico Olvia!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.57,0:05:00.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You kept denying your connection to the Ohara scholars, and yet, here you are. - OG}You kept denying any connection\Nto the Oharan scholars, yet here you are.{Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:05.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It looks like you're telling us where you're from. - OG}It's almost as if you're telling us\Nthis is where you call home...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.45,0:05:10.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And that the scholars here are commiting\Nthe same crimes as you were. - OG}and that the scholars here are\Nguilty of the same crimes as you.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.92,0:05:14.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This proves nothing of the sort. - OG}Just my being here\Nisn't proof enough for that.{Z}{Just my being here\Ndoesn't prove something like that. - Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.71,0:05:18.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you've come up with lots of excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:21.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're a smart woman, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.18,0:05:23.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But none of that matters anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.18,0:05:26.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We have no need to prove\Nyour connection to Ohara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.81,0:05:29.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If we dig up every nook and cranny of this island... - OG}If we dig up every square meter of this island,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.56,0:05:33.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{the evidence of your research on\Nthe poneglyphs will turn up in no time. - OG}evidence of your poneglyph\Nresearch is bound to turn up.{Z/rangicus}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:37.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The government estimates a 100 percent\Nprobability of this outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:42.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{For six long years, you escaped from sea to sea. - OG}For six years now you've eluded us\Nat every turn, escaping from sea to sea.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.66,0:05:45.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To capture you like we did was just the encouragement the government needed. - OG}{Capturing you will be\Na morale boost for the government. - Z}Capturing you is just\Nthe start for the government.{PJ/Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.74,0:05:50.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There are plenty of poneglyph researchers across the world. - OG}{We've caught many poneglyph researchers around the world. - Evo: combining this one with the next line to capture all the meanings while retaining proper flow & CPS}We've apprehended many\Na poneglyph researcher across the world,{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:53.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whenever we caught one, we tried hard to find their connection to Ohara. - OG}{Every single one, we investigated for a connection to Ohara. - Evo: combining this one with the next line to capture all the meanings while retaining proper flow & CPS}each time searching for a connection to Ohara.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:55.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Can you guess why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.79,0:05:58.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't tell me...\Nthey plan to use Ohara as a warning?! - OG}No...! You'll make an example of Ohara?!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.38,0:06:00.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.84,0:06:05.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If Ohara, the holy land of archaeology, were to be destroyed, it'd send a message to all other scholars. - OG}{\q2}If the holy land of archaeology were destroyed,\Nall scholars would get the message.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.14,0:06:11.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then the world will realize what will happen to those who dare\Nto research the Void Century. - OG}Then the world would see what happens\Nto those who dare research the Void Century!{Z/rangicus}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.73,0:06:15.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then... those Marine Battleships\Nthat are standing by, just off shore... -OG}Then, those Marine battleships standing by...{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.36,0:06:19.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey now... Just how much do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:21.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:25.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They are there to ensure\Nthat not one criminal escapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.91,0:06:29.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But to make it seem legitimate,\Nwe must first verify a crime has been commited. - OG}But for legitimacy, we must first verify\Na crime has been committed.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.79,0:06:32.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We're not pirates, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.04,0:06:35.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And that's why I came all this way... - OG}That's why I came all this way.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:40.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{to conduct a deep investigation on this island and evacuate those who have nothing to do with this. - OG}{\q2}I need to conduct a thorough investigation\Nof the island and evacuate those who aren't involved.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.76,0:06:42.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.47,0:06:44.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Get her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:59.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop it! The books here\Nare a world treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.32,0:07:01.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Someone's still here?! Take him outside! - OG}Another one?! Take him outside!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:01.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Come with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.94,0:07:03.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit, you bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.86,0:07:05.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There must be a hidden room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:07.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Find it! - OG}{Don't let up until you find it! - Z}Make sure you find it!{Panda}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:13.96,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,This is terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.46,0:07:18.83,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{The battleships are already visible! - OG}The battleships are already within sight!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.42,0:07:22.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is this all of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.00,0:07:25.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Now, gather all the scholars here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.38,0:07:27.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Look. The scholars have been captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:29.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What could they have done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.43,0:07:32.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They said the scholars\Nwanted to destroy the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.14,0:07:33.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That can't be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.35,0:07:35.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Where's the evacuation ship?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:37.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's at the western shore! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:40.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry up and go!\NHurry to the western shore! - OG}Hurry up and get to the western shore!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:41.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.57,0:07:43.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There's an evacuation ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.57,0:07:46.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There's no telling what the government will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:48.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You should head that way, too. - OG}Hurry and head that way too!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.41,0:07:51.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No! Even if I get on that ship,\Nthe people there won't be nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:53.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm staying here with you guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:54.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.62,0:07:55.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Just like you guys, I'm a–
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.87,0:07:57.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Just go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.42,0:08:02.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Working hard, men?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.21,0:08:04.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Thank you for taking the time to come here, Chief! - OG}– We appreciate the visit, Chief!\N– We appreciate the visit, Chief!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:10.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Anyway, I never expected to run\Ninto a ferocious animal here. - OG}I tell you, this is the last place\NI expected to run into a ferocious animal.{Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.22,0:08:16.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I nearly died. - OG}I was nearly killed.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:18.69,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.69,0:08:20.52,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Olvia-[/i1]san[/i0]! - OG}Olvia...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:22.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All right, listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.73,0:08:24.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This woman is a fugitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:28.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The group she belonged to was recently executed for\Ndeciphering the ancient texts. - OG}Her companions were recently put to death\Nfor deciphering the ancient script.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.95,0:08:32.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,However, we still don't know\Nwho the ringleader is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.28,0:08:38.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, if you guys are connected\Nto this woman, this will go much smoother. - OG}Of course, if you guys are connected\Nto this woman, this will go much smoother.{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:42.84,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{How terrible of them to hurt a woman like that. - OG}They're treating her so cruelly...{Z- used pronoun "her" to reduce redundancy with previuos line}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.84,0:08:46.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin, go to the evacuation ship. Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.80,0:08:47.63,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.14,0:08:54.51,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.35,0:08:58.93,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,You've...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.77,0:09:06.28,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,gotten so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.36,0:09:09.24,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:14.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wh-What have they done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:16.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Have they no respect for the library?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.99,0:09:19.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think that they'd take\Nsuch drastic measures...! - OG}To think they'd take things this far...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.54,0:09:22.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whoa... they've made a big show. - OG}{Oh! That was good and flashy! - Z}Oh, what a spectacle!{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:27.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hello? Is this the chief?! - OG}{\i1}Hello? Is this the chief?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.00,0:09:28.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.21,0:09:30.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.05,0:09:31.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/i1] - In the basement there's... - OG}{Hidden in the basement, - Z}{\i1}In a hidden room underground,{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:36.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/i1] - a secret room that has a big stone resembling a poneglyph and research papers regarding the ancient texts! - OG}{there's a large stone resembling a poneglyph\Nand research papers regarding ancient texts! - Z}{\i1\q2}there are research papers on ancient texts\Nand a large stone believed to be a poneglyph!{Panda/Z - word order changed to help the plural verb not sit so awkwardly next to a singular noun phrase}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.47,0:09:38.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All right. Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.02,0:09:44.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, scholars of Ohara! - OG}Well then, scholars of Ohara...{Panda}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.40,0:09:48.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Your death sentence has now been decided! - OG}that means you all get the death sentence!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:55.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's indeed regrettable... that the world's best archaeologists\Nlose their lives together today. - OG}{It is indeed regrettable that the world's best archaeologists\Nwill all lose their lives today. - Evo}{\q2}It is indeed regrettable that the world's\Npremier archaeologists will lose their lives today.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.12,0:10:02.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{See? What a letdown. - OG}Man, what a letdown.{Z/Panda/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.12,0:10:04.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That was all I had to do! - OG}My job's done here!{Z/Panda/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:06.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All that's left is to report this to the Five Elders. - OG}All I can do now\Nis report it to the Five Elders.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:07.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.34,0:10:12.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Professor! Are they really going to\Nkill you guys?! They're lying, right?! - OG}Professor, are they really going\Nto kill you?! They're lying, right?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:15.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All because you can read the ancient texts? Why?! - OG}{Just because you can\Nread ancient texts?! Why?! - Z}Just for reading ancient text?! Why?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.43,0:10:17.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Idiot! You brat! - OG}You dumb brat!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.56,0:10:23.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The purpose of their research is to revive\Na powerful weapon and commit mass murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.73,0:10:26.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's not true!\NThat isn't their intention! - OG}That's a lie! That's not at all what they're doing!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.48,0:10:28.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin, stop it. - OG}Robin, please stop.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He won't understand.\NHe's just an errand boy. - OG}As an errand boy, he wouldn't understand.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:31.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.86,0:10:35.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is it really the weapon itself\Nthat the government is afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.74,0:10:36.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Professor!\N– Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:38.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's connected, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:39.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This is good timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.79,0:10:41.54,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.54,0:10:46.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Let me speak to the Five Elders,\Nthe world's leaders, before I die. - OG}If I'm doomed to die, let me first speak\Nto the Five Elders, the world's leaders.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.54,0:10:50.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We, the scholars of Ohara, have continued our research for a long time, - OG}We, the scholars of Ohara,\Nhave dedicated many years to our research,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:54.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and although our research isn't finished yet, we formed a hypothesis about the Void Century. - OG}and while we must stop halfway now,\Nwe have a hypothesis about the Void Century.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:56.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So, I'd like to report it to them. - OG}I'd like to report it to them.{Evo: nothing preceding this really warranted a "so" here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:10:58.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What rubbish... - OG}What a waste of time....{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.76,0:10:59.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.43,0:10:59.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:02.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin, get away from here now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.93,0:11:05.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Listening to what I'm about to say is a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.44,0:11:08.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.11,0:11:11.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, apparently the scholars\Nhave been found guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:12.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.57,0:11:16.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey! Marine battleships are\Nsailing this way from the east!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.91,0:11:20.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They're gonna do something!\NLet's hurry to the evacuation ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.78,0:11:22.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wh-What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:23.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's a giant!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:29.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.00,0:11:33.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You need to hurry up\Nand escape from this island! - OG}You need to hurry\Nand escape from this island!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:41.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Has the buster call been enacted yet? - OG}Has the buster call been sounded yet?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:43.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We're still on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:45.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.60,0:11:47.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Run to the evacuation ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.19,0:11:53.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So this is a poneglyph, huh? - OG}So this is a poneglyph?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.69,0:11:58.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah. Apparently if we were to try and\Nblow it up, it wouldn't get a scratch. - OG}Yeah. Apparently, even explosives\Nwon't put a scratch on this thing.{Z/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:00.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What a creepy stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.32,0:12:03.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I can't believe these things\Nare scattered around the world.{OG}{I can't believe\Nthese things are all over the world. - Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.74,0:12:05.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.29,0:12:07.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yes, they deserve the death penalty. - OG}Yes, they will receive the death penalty.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:11.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since we seized the evidence,\Nwe'll carry out your orders. - OG}We've seized all the evidence,\Nso now we'll carry out your next order.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:13.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It cannot be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.84,0:12:18.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is quite unfortunate;\Nhowever, they violated the world's laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.47,0:12:20.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We cannot overlook it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.68,0:12:24.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Cut the transparent pleasantries, Five Elders!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.43,0:12:25.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:26.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't be rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.89,0:12:29.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You're talking to the leaders of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.85,0:12:33.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Is this Ohara's Professor Clover,\Nthe authority of archaeology? - OG}Is this Ohara's Professor Clover,\Nthe eminent authority on archaeology?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.48,0:12:39.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{I know your name well, since you've\Ncontributed to the world's culture. - OG}{\q2}Your reputation precedes you,\Ngiven your world-renowned cultural contributions.{Z/AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:42.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}To think that someone of your caliber\Nwould take the wrong path...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.49,0:12:45.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The past belongs to all mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:52.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No one has the right to stop us\Nfrom wanting to know our unspoken history!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.54,0:12:53.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.50,0:12:57.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Deciphering the poneglyphs makes it\Npossible to revive the ancient weapon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.76,0:12:59.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{which puts the world in danger. - OG}bringing danger upon this world.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.97,0:13:06.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Even if your research has the best of intentions, all it takes is for someone to come along and use your research. - OG}Though your intentions are pure, it only takes\None person to find and abuse your research.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.47,0:13:13.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/q2]No matter what happened in the past, if humans\Ncreated that history, we should accept all of it. - OG}No matter what happened in the past,\Nwe must accept it as our shared history.{Gaijin/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.69,0:13:18.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If we fearlessly learn all we can,\Nwe will find solutions no matter what happens. - OG}If we fearlessly learn all we can,\Nwe will be ready for any future incidents.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:19.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{That's an idealistic argument. - OG}How idealistic.{Z - I know this removes the translated "argument" but I think that meaning can be implied from the fact that we just heard Clover arguing his case. Now we have an agreeable CPS.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.61,0:13:21.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.07,0:13:24.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Isn't that reasoning\Njust a convenient excuse for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:28.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Of the facts that still remain, - OG}{Of the remaining, unanswered questions, - Z}Of the remaining unanswered\Nquestions about this world,{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.58,0:13:34.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,we are most interested in the poneglyphs\Nand the very reason for their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.34,0:13:42.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why did the ancients take the trouble\Nto inscribe the text on hard stones in order to pass it down to the future? - OG}{[/q2]Why did the ancients inscribe the text on such hard stones\Nwhen leaving their messages for the future? - Z}{\q2}Why would the ancients take the trouble to etch their\Nmessages for future generations on such durable stone...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:46.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They inscribed history on unbreakable stones... and scattered them around the world. -OG}inscribing history upon unbreakable stones\Nand scattering them around the world?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:54.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Is it not because they thought that their message\Nwould be eradicated if they wrote it on paper or in books?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.94,0:14:00.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In other words, it is the proof that\Nthose who left the poneglyphs clearly had an enemy. - OG}In short, it's proof that those who left\Nthe poneglyphs most certainly had an enemy.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.24,0:14:06.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say, Professor Clover?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.20,0:14:11.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Assuming they were destroyed by some enemy... -OG}If we assume these people\Nwere destroyed by said enemy,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.37,0:14:14.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{this enemy must've lived on into history. - OG}then that enemy would have lived on,\Nunopposed, in the years to follow.{Z - I can't remove the redundancy. Even in the manga, Professor Clover seems to be foot-stomping that it's this "enemy" that lived on through the years.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.79,0:14:23.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Coincidentally, just when the Void Century\Nended 800 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.43,0:14:27.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,the World Government was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:35.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If the current World Government was the enemy\Nof those that ceased to exist, - OG}If the current World Government was once\Nthe enemy of those that ceased to exist,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:42.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/q2]one could think that the Void Century is an inconvenient history\Nthat was hushed up by the World Government. - OG}{\q2}then the Void Century might be an inconvenient history,\Nbrushed under the rug by those in power.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.65,0:14:48.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{By analyzing the ancient documents\Nand some poneglyphs we could find, - OG}By analyzing the ancient documents\Nand what poneglyphs we could find,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.37,0:14:52.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{we eventually discovered\Nthe existence of a lost country. - OG}we eventually discovered\Nevidence of a lost civilization.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.33,0:14:58.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the documents brought to light\Nwas the existence of a grand kingdom. - OG}{What the documents brought to light\Nwas that there once existed a grand kingdom. - Z}The documents brought to light\Nthat there once existed a grand kingdom.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.17,0:15:01.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It seems to have boasted\Nhegemony in its time,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.17,0:15:05.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but information on this country\Nhas been obsessively erased. - OG}but information on this country\Nhas been rewritten into oblivion.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:11.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They likely anticipated their defeat\Nto the future World Government... - OG}{They likely anticipated their defeat\Nat the hands of the future World Government, - Z}{\q2}They likely anticipated defeat at the hands of the allied\Nnations who later became the World Government,{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.64,0:15:16.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and so inscribed all they knew on those\Nstones to leave their ideas to the future. - OG}and so they inscribed their truth\Nupon those stones for future generations.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.35,0:15:21.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Indeed, those stones are the poneglyphs\Nthat remain to this very day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.07,0:15:23.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:25.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a bold hypothesis. - OG}Quite a bold hypothesis...{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.15,0:15:28.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's true that the ancient weapon\Nwould threaten the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.78,0:15:34.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{However, isn't it actually that\Nthe World Government is more threatened - OG}However, isn't it actually that\Nthe World Government is more threatened
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.58,0:15:39.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,by people becoming aware\Nof that kingdom's existence and ideology?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.63,0:15:45.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We still have to analyze what this threat is, - OG}We have yet to fully analyze\Nthe nature of this threat,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.13,0:15:48.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but the name of this once-prosperous kingdom\Nthat holds the key to everything is... - OG}but this once-prosperous kingdom\Nis the key to everything!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.64,0:15:50.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but the name of this once-prosperous kingdom\Nthat holds the key to everything is... - OG}And its name was...{Z - retimed and rewritten}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.47,0:15:53.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eliminate him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:06.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.99,0:16:10.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ohara...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.16,0:16:15.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You bastards!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:15.95,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,How dare you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:18.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Professor Clover!\N– Professor Clover!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.62,0:16:21.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{...come to know too much. - OG}...has learned too much.{Evo: normally I'd prefer the OG phrasing, but the interruption from the people makes me want to simplify this to avoid potential confusion.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:25.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Give the attack signal. - OG}Signal the attack.{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:28.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.01,0:16:30.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No one leaves the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.48,0:16:42.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Now, with this golden transponder snail,\Nwhich Admiral Sengoku has entrusted to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:43.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:45.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.53,0:16:48.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You fool! You shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:49.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.15,0:16:51.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'll initiate a buster call!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.74,0:16:53.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Farewell, Ohara. - OG}{Say your goodbyes. - Z}It's out of my hands now.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.45,0:16:56.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,He did something!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:17:00.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hurry to the evacuation ship, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.62,0:17:02.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No! I don't wanna be alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:06.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't say such a foolish thing at a time like this. - OG}This is no time for foolish sentiments!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:08.63,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:14.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}That's the buster call order!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All battleships, to your positions!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.64,0:17:18.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Prepare to open fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:21.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.02,0:17:23.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.11,0:17:25.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Knowledge is on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:29.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, World Government! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:32.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Taking our lives should be enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.95,0:17:36.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't look at me. It must've caught fire\Nfrom the explosions earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:40.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This isn't a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.62,0:17:44.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea how many\Nscholarly treasures are in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.21,0:17:44.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Hey! Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.71,0:17:47.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ah. We don't need guns anymore. - OG}Listen. We don't need guns anymore.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.76,0:17:50.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Those from the government, pull out. - OG}Government agents, clear out!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.38,0:17:53.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and get the books!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:57.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Put out the fire in the library!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.40,0:18:10.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Form a bucket brigade!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.11,0:18:14.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Get the books outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.55,0:18:30.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bring that woman with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.63,0:18:32.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Come. - OG}Come on.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.22,0:18:37.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There's a piece of information that only she knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.43,0:18:40.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll cause a problem if she dies here. - OG}We can't have her dying here.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.31,0:18:45.44,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.44,0:18:51.32,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.32,0:18:54.07,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Please... make sure you escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.07,0:18:56.41,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't die, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.28,0:18:58.70,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Nose! Nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.33,0:19:04.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Robin! Hurry! -OG}{Robin! Don't tarry! - Z}Robin, make haste!{Panda}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.54,0:19:06.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Get out of here now! - OG}Hurry and leave!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.30,0:19:12.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Robin{-chan}!\N– Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.26,0:19:23.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Are you... my mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.73,0:19:31.69,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Olvia! Are you gonna come\Naboard the ship or not? - OG}Olvia! Are you coming aboard or not?{Z/Panda}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.69,0:19:33.65,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,648,1,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:35.82,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'll hold her, so go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.95,0:19:35.82,FlashbacksSecondary-207+,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:37.32,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.32,0:19:41.74,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1519)}Mommy! Mommy! Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.83,0:19:43.62,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.62,0:19:46.29,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I can never call myself your mother again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.83,0:19:52.17,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1480)}{I can't be allowed... to be your\Nmother after all these years. - OG}After all these years,\NI shouldn't even think about it.{Evo, moved line break}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.43,0:20:03.01,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,228,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}– Monster!\N– Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:05.73,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,225,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}Her mom abandoned her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.77,0:20:08.52,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,268,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}Robin! Those are my daughter's clothes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:11.11,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Aunt Roji!\NI wanted to try them on just once!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.15,0:20:14.32,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,227,\3c&H525252&\4c&H000000&)}{You eat a lot for someone who lives here free. - OG}You eat an awful lot for a freeloader.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:25.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1439)}Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.91,0:20:28.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,my mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.84,0:20:37.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What? You have a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:40.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.47,0:20:42.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia{-san}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.72,0:20:45.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.73,0:20:49.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,but I think you're confusing me\Nwith someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:55.44,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Forgive me, Robin! I don't wanna\Nmake you a criminal's daughter! - OG}I can't let you become known\Nas a criminal's daughter!{Evo, matching my edit of the edit}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.44,0:20:57.40,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.86,0:20:59.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What a weird brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.11,0:21:01.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.46,0:21:19.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:23.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I've grown, but don't you remember me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:26.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I've been waiting for you to return all this time! - OG}I've waited so long for you to come home!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.31,0:21:27.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.48,0:21:30.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,really not...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.15,0:21:33.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,my mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.15,0:21:37.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I wanted you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:39.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,to hold my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.90,0:21:43.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,and walk with me someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.49,0:21:48.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So I studied hard and was\Nable to become an archaeologist!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.54,0:21:50.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I can read poneglyphs, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.37,0:21:53.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That brat can?! - OG}That brat can do what?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.92,0:21:55.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.00,0:21:57.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.34,0:22:00.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{please let me stay... with you! - OG}please let me stay by your side!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.34,0:22:02.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mother! - OG}Mom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.97,0:22:04.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:06.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.27,0:22:09.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,don't leave me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.81,0:22:12.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,alone anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.94,0:22:18.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.11,0:22:21.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What the hell is this attack?! - OG}Why the hell are they attacking us?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.36,0:22:23.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm exercising a buster call.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:26.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Commence concerted fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.45,0:22:30.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We're targeting everything on Ohara,\Nthe island of archaeology!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.66,0:22:35.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The research by the Oharan scholars has\Nreached a level we never imagined.{Polly - Ohara -> Oharan}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.92,0:22:39.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Knowledge can be transferred.\NDon't let it out of that island. - OG}Knowledge can be transferred.\NDon't let it leave that island.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.42,0:22:45.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In the name of justice,\Nannihilate the devils living in Ohara! - OG}In the name of justice,\Nannihilate the devils of Ohara!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.72,0:22:52.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.27,0:22:56.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We haven't gotten off of the island yet!\NAre they trying to kill us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.69,0:23:00.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The Tree of Knowledge is taking direct hits!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.23,0:23:02.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There's no mistaking that this is\NHeadquarters' military power. - OG}{This is surely headquarters'\Nmilitary might. - Z}{This is surely headquarters' military might. - Evo: works a bit better without the line break imo.}The military might of Marine Headquarters...{Poppy/Z- too clunky before, so adding "Marine Headquarters" to clarify things, and probably can just imply the "no mistaking" part}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.69,0:23:05.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The government was probably\Ngoing to do this from the start. - OG}{It's likely the government was\Nplanning to do this all along. - Z}The government must have been\Nplanning to do this all along.{Evo/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.95,0:23:06.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How foolish. - OG}How senseless.{Evo/PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.99,0:23:10.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Chief, that brat said\Nthat she's an archaeologist. - OG}Chief, the brat said she's an archaeologist.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.37,0:23:14.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, she did say that.\NI don't know if it's true or not, - OG}Yeah, she did say that,\Nthough I don't know whether it's true.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.00,0:23:16.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but when we don't know,\Neliminating them solves the problem. - OG}{We can just resolve this\Nby eliminating the unknown. - Z}Eliminate her too, just in case.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.71,0:23:19.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Remember her face well so that\Nyou don't let her leave the island. - OG}{Commit her face to memory\Nso you don't let her leave the island. - Z}Remember her face and ensure\Nshe doesn't escape the island.{Poppy}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.92,0:23:21.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Retreat! - OG}Let's move!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:22.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then, I'll take Olvia. - OG}I'll take Olvia with–{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.17,0:23:27.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Forget her! No time for that now!\NJust leave her here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:30.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If we stay here, we'll get killed, too! - OG}If we stick around any longer,\Nwe're goners too!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.35,0:23:33.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My life is the most important thing! - OG}And {\i1}my{\i0} life is the most important of all!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.06,0:23:34.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All, retreat! - OG}Full retreat!{Poppy}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.56,0:23:35.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go back to the ship! - OG}Get back to the ship!{Poppy}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.24,0:23:46.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Do something about the fire in the library!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.45,0:23:48.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Protect the Tree of Knowledge!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.80,0:24:11.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I've wanted to do this... - OG}I've wanted this...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.52,0:24:16.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,for so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.56,0:24:21.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.94,0:24:25.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mother! - OG}Mom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.86,0:24:31.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's my fault, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.20,0:24:35.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is it true that you can read poneglyphs?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.45,0:24:39.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,If I had properly kept an eye on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.25,0:24:42.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.00,0:24:44.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I just wanted–
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.00,0:24:46.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm really surprised to know that you've\Nbecome able to do things like that. - OG}I can't believe how capable you've become!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.84,0:24:48.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm so proud of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.55,0:24:51.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You must've tried hard and studied a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.93,0:24:54.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's not something anyone can do. - OG}It's not something just anyone can do.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.18,0:24:55.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's amazing, Robin! - OG}You're amazing, Robin!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.48,0:25:06.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, the officials from earlier\Nare the only ones who know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.94,0:25:09.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This is no time to be sitting around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.32,0:25:11.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Olvia! Take Robin and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.87,0:25:16.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you can somehow sneak Robin onto the evacuation ship, you can leave the island! - OG}If you can sneak Robin aboard\Nthe evacuation ship, she can leave the island!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.04,0:25:20.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.87,0:25:23.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There you are! I looked all over for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.54,0:25:24.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Saul!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.71,0:25:26.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So you were able to see Olvia!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.84,0:25:27.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Saul!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.71,0:25:29.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What are you doing on this island?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.80,0:25:35.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,By some twist of fate, I got shipwrecked\Nand was saved by Robin on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.56,0:25:37.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{More importantly, the situation is terrible! - OG}Anyway, the situation is really bad!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.81,0:25:40.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You have to leave the island immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.48,0:25:41.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Please take care of Robin! - OG}Please take Robin!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.52,0:25:43.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Please let my daughter escape\Nfrom the island at any cost! - OG}My daughter {\i1}must{\i0} escape the island!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.77,0:25:44.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.86,0:25:46.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No! What about you, Mom?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.73,0:25:48.15,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Aren't you coming with me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.36,0:25:50.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Olvia... What are you gonna... - OG}Olvia, what are you...?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.07,0:25:53.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There's still something\Nthat I have to do here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.53,0:25:56.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mother! Don't leave me! - OG}Mom! Don't leave me!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.03,0:25:57.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I finally got to see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.70,0:25:59.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'll stay here too!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.12,0:26:00.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.04,0:26:04.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're an Ohara scholar,\Nso you should know this very well. - OG}{You're an Oharan scholar\Nand should understand this well. - AR}As an Oharan scholar,\Nyou should understand this well.{Z - CPS}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.04,0:26:06.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{History is the treasure of mankind. - OG}History is the legacy of mankind.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.00,0:26:09.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It will illuminate the future\Nin which your generation will live. - OG}It will illuminate the future for your generation.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.34,0:26:11.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/q2]But the history we received from the past\Nwill disappear unless we pass it on to the next era. - OG}But the history we obtained from the past...{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.34,0:26:15.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{[/q2]But the history we received from the past\Nwill disappear unless we pass it on to the next era. - OG}will disappear unless\Nwe pass it on to the next era.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.68,0:26:16.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Put out the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.51,0:26:17.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Protect the books!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.26,0:26:21.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ohara doesn't want to reveal our history. - OG}Ohara doesn't want to expose our history.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.52,0:26:24.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We just wanted to acknowledge and preserve the voices of the past. - OG}We only wished to preserve\Nthe voices of the past.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.85,0:26:27.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Our research will end now, - OG}Our research ends here...{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.27,0:26:30.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,but even if Ohara is obliterated...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.15,0:26:37.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{we cannot give up the future\Nyou young ones will live in! - OG}we cannot forsake\Nthe future of your generation!{Z}{Enies 10 - 10:31}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.24,0:26:40.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I don't understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.70,0:26:44.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You will understand someday. - OG}You will... someday.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.84,0:26:49.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Now, go, Saul!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.84,0:26:53.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.42,0:26:54.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.18,0:26:58.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't wanna go!\NI'll stay with you, Mother! - OG}I don't wanna go!\NI wanna stay with you, Mom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.89,0:27:01.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Mother! - OG}Mom!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.31,0:27:04.14,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I was happy to hear you call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.94,0:27:06.31,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:10.15,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,From now on, for you and me both...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.15,0:27:11.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Live, Robin!{Enies 10 - 04:06}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.00,0:27:29.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.00,0:27:31.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral! Vice Admiral Kuzan!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.75,0:27:33.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.09,0:27:35.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,On the island... Yes, there's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.72,0:27:37.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So what's the matter?! - OG}What's the matter?!{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.72,0:27:39.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Just spit it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.39,0:27:42.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's the deserter, Vice Admiral Saul!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.06,0:27:44.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Saul! Go back! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.39,0:27:46.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No! I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.23,0:27:49.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Robin! Hold your head high, Robin!{Enies 10 - 10:28}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.65,0:27:51.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Your mom is honorable!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.57,0:27:53.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ohara is honorable!{Enies 10 - 10:29}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.61,0:27:58.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Someday, pass down\Nthis island's history, Robin!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.11,0:28:01.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Ohara fought against the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.45,0:28:05.91,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.91,0:28:07.50,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Capturing them is enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.04,0:28:12.88,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're not even violent pirates!\NAre you so weak that you can't suppress them?! - OG}{They aren't exactly bloodthirsty pirates!\NAre you too weak to overpower them?! - Z}They aren't exactly bloodthirsty pirates!\NAre you too weak to capture them alive?!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.55,0:28:16.72,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've caught history exploration ships many times, - OG}We've captured many ships\Nthat were on history expeditions,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.72,0:28:20.68,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{but I don't understand why they had to die. - OG}{but I never understood\Nwhy their crews had to be killed. - Z}but I don't understand\Nwhy this crew had to die.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.01,0:28:24.39,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Vice Admiral Saul!\NWe found one survivor! - OG}Vice Admiral Saul! We found a lone survivor!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.10,0:28:26.60,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{How dare you kill my fellow scholars?! - OG}You killed my associates!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.02,0:28:30.56,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Do you really want the weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.94,0:28:32.02,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,What pitiful people...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.65,0:28:34.57,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{You don't have your own will and \Nyet you cast judgment on us... - OG}You're just tools, yet you judge us...{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.57,0:28:36.03,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey! He's a vice admiral!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.03,0:28:39.53,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{not doubting laws and saying it's to\Nprevent the revival of the weapon! - OG}...blindly believing your justice\Nprevents the weapon's revival!{Z/Poppy}{...while pretending your justice\Nwill prevent a weapon's revival! - Evo: I also considered like "...blindly trusting your superiors'\Nfacade about the weapon's revival!}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.62,0:28:45.62,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1481)}{You're just frightened by the history\Nthat you don't even know! - OG}You're terrified of a history\Nyou don't even understand!{Evo/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.16,0:28:47.62,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,This is a top-secret mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.62,0:28:49.79,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,A buster call?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.21,0:28:55.34,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Five vice admirals command ten battleships in a buster call. I want you to be one of them. - OG}{Five vice admirals command ten battleships in an all-out assault. - Evo}{\q2}Five vice admirals command ten battleships\Nin an all-out assault, and I want you to be one of them.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.34,0:28:57.09,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,They are just scholars!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.09,0:28:59.09,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Why do we have to go that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.09,0:29:05.10,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Those scholars that we've captured, too! They look like they just really want to know the history to me! - OG}Even all the ones we've captured just\Nseemed really intent on studying history!{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.10,0:29:09.06,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{If their research is so dangerous,\Nthe government should help them too! - OG}{If their research is dangerous,\Nthe government should lend a helping hand! - Z}If their research is dangerous,\Nthe government should help them out!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.06,0:29:11.98,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're the ones who actually have to kill people! - OG}My men and I will be\Nthe ones taking their lives...{Z/Panda}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.31,0:29:15.40,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Give me the proof that they're completely evil! - OG}so give me some kind of proof\Nthat they're evil!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.40,0:29:18.44,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Are you doubting the government?\NShut up and follow orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.41,0:29:24.99,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I'd like...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.83,0:29:27.20,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,to ask you some questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.20,0:29:31.17,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,This is an emergency! Vice Admiral Saul\Ntook a criminal and deserted!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.17,0:29:35.63,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,He knows everything about the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.96,0:29:38.84,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,After them! Capture Saul and Olvia without fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.47,0:29:40.97,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{You can shoot them if needed! - OG}Shoot them if needed!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.59,0:29:42.84,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Pursuers are coming! - OG}We're being chased!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.84,0:29:44.80,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll deal with them! - OG}I'll handle them!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.80,0:29:47.77,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{You'll never be able\Nto go back to the Marines, Saul. - OG}You'll never be able\Nto return to the Marines, Saul.{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.77,0:29:49.02,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.02,0:29:52.73,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I can't stay in the Marines\Nhaving this sense of distrust. - OG}I can't stay in the Marines\Nif I can't even trust them.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.10,0:29:57.36,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Even if they're obeying the law,\Nthis operation is too tyrannical. - OG}This may be a government-sanctioned action,\Nbut this operation is too tyrannical.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.36,0:29:59.61,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm just following my sense of justice. - OG}I need to follow my own sense of justice.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.61,0:30:02.45,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{Now, hurry to your homeland\Nto let people know. - OG}Now, hurry to your homeland\Nto inform everyone.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.45,0:30:04.07,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm not gonna thank you for this. - OG}I'm not thanking you for this.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.07,0:30:06.16,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.62,0:30:11.29,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&\t(0,271,1,\3c&H000000&\4c&H000000&)}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.50,0:30:16.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They're aiming at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.84,0:30:22.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Saul!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.55,0:30:24.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Ah! It hit him! - OG}Oh! It hit him!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.01,0:30:25.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.09,0:30:28.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't apologize! He's already those evil people's accomplice! - OG}Don't apologize! He's already\Nan accomplice of those evildoers!{Z}{Don't apologize!\NHe deserted to help out those devils! - Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.47,0:30:30.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.48,0:30:32.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That must've scared you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.77,0:30:35.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.02,0:30:37.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That must be it! - OG}It was you...!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.02,0:30:38.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Firing this close? - OG}Firing at this close range?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.40,0:30:41.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What if you had hurt Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.03,0:30:43.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Vice Admiral! Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.53,0:30:44.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.74,0:30:49.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't know what justice is in this situation,\Nso I'll just protect my friend! - OG}{I'm a little fuzzy on justice in this situation,\Nso I'll just protect my friend! - Z}I don't know what justice is in this situation,\Nbut I know I should protect my friend!{AR}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.62,0:30:51.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Saul!{Enies 10 - 01:50}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.21,0:30:53.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You better be ready! - OG}Get ready!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.58,0:31:00.25,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Make an enemy of me, and I'll make you pay! - OG}Making an enemy of me\Nwill be the last thing you do!{Z}
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=13}===============================DIALOGUE============================
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=10}============================SIGNS AND TITLE=========================
